{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{EpicodePrevNext|\nprevcode=XY064 |\nprevtitle=Battling with Elegance and a Big Smile! |\nnextcode=XY065 |\nnexttitle=Good Friends, Great Training! |\nseries=XY series |\ncolorscheme=Kalos}}\n{{EpisodeInfobox|\nepcode=XYS03 |\ncolorscheme=Kalos |\ntitle_en=Mega Evolution Special III|\ntitle_ja=ポケットモンスターXY特別編 最強メガシンカ ～Act III～|\ntitle_ja_trans=Pocket Monsters XY Special Episode: The Strongest Mega Evolution ~Act III~ |\nscreen=hd|\nbroadcast_jp=March 19, 2015 |\nbroadcast_us=August 15, 2015  |\nen_op=None |\nen_ed=Mega Evolution Theme |\nja_op=None |\nja_ed=[[V (Volt)|メガＶ（メガボルト）]] |\nolmteam= |\nscenario=冨岡淳広 |\nstoryboardn=1 |\nstoryboard=浅田裕二 |\ndirectorn=1 |\ndirector=浅田裕二 |\nartn=4 |\nart=岩根雅明  |\nart2=中矢利子|\nart3=松永香苗|\nart4=志村泉|\nmorecredits=no |<!--please don\'t change to "yes" until the corresponding staff page has been updated-->\nepstaffpage=|\nfootnotes=*{{filb-eppics|xy|SP3}}\n* {{BMGf|174005|Preview thread on BMGf}} \'\'Closed\'\'\n* {{BMGf|174009|Original review thread on BMGf}}\n* {{BMGf|198828|Dub review thread on BMGf}}\n}}\n\n\'\'\'Pokémon: Mega Evolution Special III\'\'\' (Japanese: \'\'\'ポケットモンスターXY特別編 最強メガシンカ ～Act III～\'\'\' \'\'Pocket Monsters XY Special Episode: The Strongest Mega Evolution ~Act III~\'\') is the third [[Mega Evolution Specials|Mega Evolution Special]] and the third special episode of the {{series|XY}}. It first aired in Japan on March 19, 2015 and in the United States on August 15, 2015.\n{{spoilers}}\n\n==Other posters and logos==\n<gallery>\nFile:XYS03 poster.png|Poster\nFile:XYS03 logo JP.png|Logo\n</gallery>\n\n==Blurb==\n<!--http://web.archive.org/web/20180518182537/https://www.pokemon.com/us/pokemon-episodes/-->\n<i>In this third installment of the four-part series, Alain, Mairin, and Steven arrive at the Devon Corporation in Rustboro City, where they make contact with Alain’s boss, Lysandre. Lysandre informs the trio that Primal Groudon and Primal Kyogre have appeared and are both moving towards a mysterious energy source that is suspected to be the missing Giant Rock.\n\nSteven recounts the legend of the ancient times when Groudon and Kyogre struggled against each other to expand the continents and the seas. The two battled over a source of enormous energy with such ferocity that it nearly destroyed the world. Unfortunately, this legend seems to be playing out again!\n\nSteven analyzes the Legendary Pokémon’s separate paths towards the Giant Rock and determines that they will cross paths in the ocean off the coast of Rustboro City. Despite Mairin’s objections, Alain and Steven travel to the meeting point to observe as the two Pokémon collide near the Giant Rock and engage in an epic battle. Lysandre gives Alain orders to protect the Giant Rock at all costs.\n\nAlain and Steven send Mega Charizard X and Mega Metagross out to battle Primal Groudon and Primal Kyogre, but they prove to be a mere distraction. The situation seems bleak—particularly when Mega Rayquaza arrives to join this all-out battle! Just as it appears that Mega Rayquaza will claim the Giant Rock, a submarine emerges from beneath the waves and pulls the Giant Rock into its hull via a powerful energy shield.\n\nLysandre contacts Steven from the submarine, confirming that he’s taking the Giant Rock to Kalos. As the situation settles, Alain leaves Mairin to return to Lysandre Labs to continue his training, but Steven and Mairin decide to follow their friend.</i>\n\n==Plot==\n{{incomplete plot}}\n\n==Major events==\n<!-- This is not for summarizing everything that happens in this episode. Only events pertaining to the series as a whole, such as catching and releasing Pokémon and obtaining Badge, go here.-->\n* [[Alain]], [[Mairin]], and {{Steven}} arrive in [[Rustboro City]].\n* Alain and Steven battle [[Primal Reversion|Primal]] {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Groudon (XY)|Groudon}} and Primal {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Kyogre (XY)|Kyogre}}.\n* [[Mega Evolution|Mega]] {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Rayquaza}} reappears, stopping the rampage between Primal Groudon and Primal Kyogre.\n* [[Lysandre]] obtains the legendary [[Giant Rock]].\n* {{an|Professor Sycamore}} learns that Alain can use Mega Evolution.\n* Alain separates from Mairin and returns to [[Lysandre Labs]] to train.\n* Mairin returns to [[Kalos]] with Steven to search for Alain.\n{{animeevents}}\n\n===Debuts===\n====Pokémon debuts====\n* [[Primal Reversion|Primal]] {{p|Kyogre}}\n* [[Primal Reversion|Primal]] {{p|Groudon}}\n\n==Characters==\n===Humans===\n* [[Alain]]\n* [[Mairin]]\n* [[Steven Stone]]\n* {{an|Professor Sycamore}} \n* [[Lysandre]]\n* Operator\n* Operator A\n* Operator B\n\n===Pokémon===\n* {{p|Charizard}} ({{OP|Alain|Charizard}}; [[Mega Evolution|Mega Charizard X]])\n* {{p|Chespin}} ([[Mairin]]\'s; [[Chespie]])\n* {{p|Metagross}} ({{OP|Steven|Metagross}}; [[Mega Evolution|Mega Metagross]]; {{shiny}})\n* {{p|Garchomp}} ({{an|Professor Sycamore}}\'s)\n* {{p|Pyroar}} ({{OP|Lysandre|Pyroar}}; male)\n* {{p|Jigglypuff}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Roserade}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Sableye}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Makuhita}} (Trainer\'s; ×2)\n* {{p|Doduo}} (Trainer\'s; multiple)\n* {{p|Azumarill}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Treecko}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Torchic}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Mudkip}} (Trainer\'s)\n* {{p|Tyranitar}} (Trainer\'s; [[Mega Evolution|Mega Tyranitar]])\n* {{p|Rayquaza}} ([[Mega Evolution|Mega Rayquaza]]; {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Rayquaza|anime}})\n* {{p|Kyogre}} ([[Primal Reversion|Primal Kyogre]]; {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Kyogre (XY)|anime}})\n* {{p|Groudon}} ([[Primal Reversion|Primal Groudon]]; {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Groudon (XY)|anime}})\n\n==Cast==\n{{cast/h|Kalos}}\n{{cast|Kalos|Alain|Jonathan Silver|Alain|Kenshō Ono|アラン|小野賢章|top=yes}}\n{{cast|Kalos|Mairin|Zoe Martin|Manon|Mikako Komatsu|マノン|小松未可子}}\n{{cast|Kalos|Narrator|disp=Narration|H.D. Quinn|Narration|Hideaki Tezuka|ナレーション|手塚秀彰|bottom=yes}}\n! colspan=6 | {{color|FFF|Special appearances by}}\n|-\n{{cast|Kalos|Lysandre|H.D. Quinn|Fleur-de-lis|Hideaki Tezuka|フラダリ|手塚秀彰|top=yes}}\n{{cast|Kalos|Steven Stone|Andrew Paull|Daigo Tsuwabuki|Kenichi Suzumura|ツワブキ・ダイゴ|鈴村健一}}\n{{cast|Kalos|Professor Sycamore (anime)|disp=Professor Sycamore|Jake Paque|Platane|Hiroshi Tsuchida|プラターヌ|土門大|bottom=yes}}\n|}\n<!--\n==Staff==-->\n\n==Trivia== \n* This special aired between [[XY064]] and [[XY065]] in Japan.\n* This episode was skipped in {{pmin|Canada}} due to \'\'[[XY076|A Not-So-Flying Start!]]\'\' airing in place of it; it eventually aired in Canada on December 26, 2015.\n\n===Errors===\n* When [[Mega Evolution|Mega]] {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Rayquaza}} is about to launch {{m|Hyper Beam}}, its middle right claw is colored green rather than white.\n\n<gallery>\nFile:XYS03 error.png|The coloring error\n</gallery>\n\n===Dub edits===\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Epilang|color=F16A81|bordercolor=025DA6\n|zh_yue={{tt|最強超進化～第三章～|The Strongest Mega Evolution~ Act III~}}{{tt|*|Anime}}<br>{{tt|最強超進化|The Strongest Mega Evolution}}{{tt|*|Official website}}\n|zh_cmn={{tt|特別篇\u3000最強超進化～第三章～|Special Episode The Strongest Mega Evolution~ Act III~}}\n|fr_eu={{tt|Pokémon : Méga-Évolution 3|Pokémon: Mega Evolution 3}} {{tt|*|Pokémon TV}}<br>{{tt|Mega évolution - Episode Spécial III|Mega Evolution - Special Episode III}}\n|de={{tt|Pokémon: Mega-Entwicklung – Sonderfolge III|Pokémon: Mega Evolution - Special Episode III}} {{tt|*|Pokémon TV}}<br>{{tt|Mega-Entwicklung - Sonderfolge III|Mega Evolution - Special Episode III}}\n|it={{tt|Episodio speciale III della miniserie Pokémon Megaevoluzione|Special episode III of the Mega Evolution Pokémon miniseries}} {{tt|*|Pokémon TV}}<br>{{tt|Megaevoluzione - Episodio Speciale III|Mega Evolution - Special Episode III}}\n|ko={{tt|최강 메가진화 ACT III|The Strongest Mega Evolution Act III}}\n|es_eu={{tt|Megaevolución. Episodio especial III|Mega Evolution. Spe